"kui väljanimele on lisatud \"String\", rakenduse pakutaval kujul ja keeles."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updating your data"
msgstr "Andmete uuendamine"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:458
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Having data in an industry standard format does give you the ability to "
#| "modify it outside the &kappname; application. DO NOT DO IT unless you "
#| "really know what you are doing, and always be certain to make a backup "
#| "copy of your data first. If you get it wrong, &kappname; may not be able "
#| "to access your data, and you could even end up losing it altogether. You "
#| "have been warned!"
msgid ""
"Having data in an industry standard format does give you the ability to "
"modify it outside the &kmymoney; application. DO NOT DO IT unless you really "
"know what you are doing, and always be certain to make a backup copy of your "
"data first. If you get it wrong, &kmymoney; may not be able to access your "
"data, and you could even end up losing it altogether. You have been warned!"
msgstr ""
"Andmete hoidmine standardses vormingus lubab sul neid muuta ka väljaspool "
"&kappname;. ÄRA TEE SEDA, kui sa ei ole kindel, et tead päris täpselt, mida "
"ette võtad, ning alati tee kindlasti kõigepealt oma andmetest varukoopia. "
"Kui midagi läheb viltu, ei pruugi &kappname; olla isegi võimeline sinu "
"andmetele ligi pääsema ning sa võid neist sootuks ilma jääda. Sind on "
"hoiatatud!"

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stored queries"
msgstr "Salvestatud päringud"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:468
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Most database systems allow you to store commonly used queries and "
#| "procedures, and in some cases, these may be held as tables or other "
#| "objects within your database itself. As you will have guessed from the "
#| "above, all the tables used by &kappname; begin with the lowercase letters "
#| "'kmm'. This standard will be maintained, and only tables beginning with "
#| "these letters will be updated. Thus, provided you avoid these in the "
#| "naming of your queries &etc;, you should not experience any problems."
msgid ""
"Most database systems allow you to store commonly used queries and "
"procedures, and in some cases, these may be held as tables or other objects "
"within your database itself. As you will have guessed from the above, all "
"the tables used by &kmymoney; begin with the lowercase letters "
"'<literal>kmm</literal>'. This standard will be maintained, and only tables "
"beginning with these letters will be updated. Thus, provided you avoid these "
"in the naming of your queries &etc;, you should not experience any problems."
msgstr ""
"Enamik andmebaasisüsteeme lubab salvestada levinumaid päringuid ja "
"protseduure ning mõnel juhul hoitakse neid lausa tabelite või muude "
"objektidena andmebaasis endas. Nagu eelnevast võis juba oletada, algavad "
"kõik tabelid, mida &kappname; kasutab, väikeste tähtedega \"kmm\". Sellest "
"standardist tuleks kinni pidada ning uuendataksegi ainult tabeleid, mis "
"nende tähtedega algavad. Eeldusel, et sa oled neid oma päringutele nime "
"andes vältinud, ei tohiks mingeid probleeme esineda."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manual database creation"
msgstr "Andmebaasi loomine käsitsi"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section covers more advanced database usage and may be skipped by the "
"general user."
msgstr ""
"Siin kõneldakse kogenumatele kasutajatele mõeldud andmebaaside kasutamise "
"viisidest, mille tavalised kasutajad võivad vahele jätta."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "When to use"
msgstr "Millal kasutada"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:488
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "There may be occasions when &kappname; is unable to create the database "
#| "automatically, or creates it without some options required by the user. "
#| "For example, the database system used may not completely conform to "
#| "standard SQL usage, or support may be introduced for new systems which "
#| "have not been fully tested in &kappname;."
msgid ""
"There may be occasions when &kmymoney; is unable to create the database "
"automatically, or creates it without some options required by the user. For "
"example, the database system used may not completely conform to standard SQL "
"usage, or support may be introduced for new systems which have not been "
"fully tested in &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Võib esineda juhtumeid, mil &kappname; ei suuda andmebaasi automaatselt luua "
"või loob selle ilma mõningate kasutajale vajalike valikuteta. Näiteks ei "
"pruugi andmebaasisüsteem täielikult ühilduda standardse SQL-i kasutamisega "
"või lisandub uute süsteemide toetus, mida &kappname;s ei ole veel "
"põhjalikult testitud."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:496
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Prior to using this facility, you should try just creating the database "
#| "entry itself (&ie; with the CREATE DATABASE statement). Provided the "
#| "database exists, &kappname; may well be able to create the tables, &etc; "
#| "in the normal database save procedure described above."
msgid ""
"Prior to using this facility, you should try just creating the database "
"entry itself (&ie; with the <literal>CREATE DATABASE</literal> statement). "
"Provided the database exists, &kmymoney; may well be able to create the "
"tables, &etc; in the normal database save procedure described above."
msgstr ""
"Enne selle võimaluse kasutamist tuleks püüa ise luua andmebaasikirje (&ie; "
"lauseega CREATE DATABASE). Kui andmebaas on olemas, võib &kappname; ehk olla "
"suuteline looma tabelid ja muu sellise tavapärase andmebaasi salvestamise "
"protseduuriga, mida kirjeldati eespool."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
